AbstractText: Two previously undescribed dihydrophenanthrene derivatives (1 and 2) were isolated along with twelve known analogues from the whole plant of Dendrobium terminale. The structures of the new compounds were elucidated on the basis of detailed spectroscopic analysis. The NMR data of known phenanthrene derivatives (7 and 9) were revised by 2D NMR. The isolated compounds were evaluated for cytotoxicity against three kinds of tumor cell lines (sw1990, HCT-116, and HepG2). Especially compounds 11 and 14 showed stronger antitumor effects, and the structure-activity relationship of these compounds was discussed.
